Object permanence test (held-out trajectories where truth has a hidden object):
  N such cases: 2595
  Of these, fraction where model put a top-2 prediction inside the occluder: 67.55%

What this number means:
  - If model has truly learned object permanence, it should put predictions inside the occluder
    when objects are there. Without memory, it can only do this when an object is *about to enter*
    (i.e., visible last frame, predicted to disappear into occluder this frame).
  - Multi-step hidden trajectories should fail.
